---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Peptide Research Notes"
description: "Research notes on commonly studied peptides, typical use cases, concentration ranges, and current price comparisons across major vendors."
---

<nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
  <a href="/">Home</a>
  <span>&rsaquo;</span>
  Research Notes
</nav>

<div class="peptides-page">
  <header class="article-header">
    <h1>Peptide Research Notes</h1>
    <p class="lede">Quick-reference notes on commonly tracked research peptides. For research use only, not medical advice.</p>
  </header>

  <h2 class="peptide-section-heading">Solo Peptides</h2>
  <div class="peptide-index-grid">
    {% for note in collections.researchNotes %}
      {% if note.data.peptideType == "single" %}
        <a href="{{ note.url }}" class="peptide-index-card">
          {{ note.data.peptideName or note.data.h1 or note.data.title }}
        </a>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <h2 class="peptide-section-heading">Common Blends</h2>
  <div class="peptide-index-grid">
    {% for note in collections.researchNotes %}
      {% if note.data.peptideType == "blend" %}
        <a href="{{ note.url }}" class="peptide-index-card">
          {{ note.data.peptideName or note.data.h1 or note.data.title }}
        </a>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <h2 class="peptide-section-heading">Research Stacks</h2>
  <div class="peptide-index-grid">
    {% for note in collections.researchNotes %}
      {% if note.data.peptideType == "stack" %}
        <a href="{{ note.url }}" class="peptide-index-card">
          {{ note.data.peptideName or note.data.h1 or note.data.title }}
        </a>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <p class="microcopy">Pages are added as research notes are completed. <a href="{{ site.appUrl }}">Open the app</a> to compare current prices.</p>
</div>
